<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1177] Upgrade to Bean Validation JSR-303 1.0 CR3 Spec API</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1177</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We need to upgrade from CR2 level of the API (geronimo-validation_1.0_spec-1.0-EA2-SNAPSHOT) to the ust released  CR3 level (geronimo-validation_1.0_spec-1.0-EA3-SNAPSHOT).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Moving from the Validation 1.0.CR2 to 1.0.CR3 levels are going to cause us some churn:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The 4 descriptor class were moved into a javax.validation.metadata package.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;A new javax.validation.Path was introduced for iterable nodes, which replaces some String usage in ConstraintViolation and TraversableResolver.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Note: Either the agimatec-validation code will need to be updated or we&apos;ll have to switch to using the RI for testing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
